<br>
   Someone else might be playing an unkempt druid, who hates mankind and civilization and wants a return to the natural order where only animals exist.<br>
<br>
   The druid might think himself neutral, others might see the druid as evil.  <br>
<br>
   A paladin might consider himself noble and just, and clearly a good person.  Other people might see him as arrogant and snobbish, and clearly wrapped up in his own self image, and serving the forces of evil more than he served those of good.<br>
<br>
   And while you'd be hard pressed to find a good character who pretends to be evil by murdering, killing, etc, is it hard to imagine an evil character who pretends to be good, only to further advance their goals?<br>
   Perhaps a dark elf rogue, who convinces a group of dwarves that he's a reformed man, and clearly does not associate himself with his evil brethren... all done in an effort to relieve the dwarves of some of their gems, and do a bit of spying for the dark empire to boot.<br>
<br>
   Would a paladin of Quellious be roleplaying better if he wrote all followers of Rallos Zek off as fiendish devils who needed to be destroyed, or offered to journey with them in an attempt to show them the happiness that a life of peace can bring a person?<br>
<br>
   My bard (neutral evil, rather selfish) will group with most anyone she doesn't find terribly displeasing.  She enjoys getting a rise out of the paladins, and thinks she's accomplished something when she can get them to behave in a hostile aggressive manner, and is always more than happy to respond to every glare and sharp word with a laugh and a smile, all with the perverse pleasure it brings her in ticking them off.<br>
   She arms her companions as much as she can.  To some people, this would be an act of selflessness.  To her, she knows that if a person has a nice sword, he's more likely to swing it.  If a person has some nice armor, they're more likely to wade into combat.  So if her friends can't equip themselves, she does her part to gear them up, all to help ensure the will and the might of Rallos Zek.<br>
<br>
   Her companions (all good and neutral) have heard whispered rumors that she (my bard) has been setting a bounty on the blood of the wood elves of Erollisi Marr, and the flesh of noble paladins who try to hold back the trollish hordes.  She (my bard) is quick to lay the blame on a dark elf who's been playing imposter in an effort to ruin her image (the guise of deception helps a lot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
   So anyways, please don't reduce this server to the simplistics of black &amp; white issues.  Characters can and should be quite complex, with a variety of motives that move them, both perceived and actual.  <br>
<br>
Syllestrae Silverblade<br>
Warchanter of Rallos Zek<br>
<br>
/em tries to imagine what the server would be like if it was 3 giant groups of players, all yelling at eachother &quot;No, WE'RE right, and YOU'RE wrong&quot;, and never going any deeper than that, and winces.  <br>
