<br>
Syllestrae is neutral evil.<br>
Starspun (her guild) is entirely neutral / good (except for her).<br>
<br>
To Starspun, she probably seems a bit overly-enthusiatic in the combat department, but has a good heart.  She's always willing to jump in to defend her guildmates, and goes out of her way to help protect them from the evils of the world whether by wading in and cutting off something's head, or providing them with the items they need to defend themselves.  To some in the guild (especially the Quellious worshippers), she's very distrusted.  They consider her a bad influence, but their teachings instruct them to give people the benefit of the doubt.  They won't waste their spells on her, but aren't opposed to journeying with her in the hopes their good behavior will rub off on her.<br>
<br>
To Syllestrae, Starspun is a guild of talented adventurers, who's skill on the battlefield would be lost if she wasn't there egging them on to cleave stuff in two.  They'd be content fishing and having picnics if someone wasn't whispering dark nothings to them.  She's had good times.  One of her favorite evenings was the night she worked Taygar, the noble scout of Tunare, into such a kobold blood frenzy that he started screaming to all who could hear him that he hated TREES.  Why would this elf hate trees?  Because the kobolds were so scared as we tore them limb from limb and showered the stonebrunt with their entrails that they kept fleeing up the trees and making it more difficult for us to hack them to pieces.<br>
<br>
What evil would it do for Syllestrae to join a band of Ogres?  They're ALREADY bloodthirsty.  She could help them wreck a few halfling houses, but really, they can do that on their own.<br>
<br>
The true tide of battle is waged when people who SHOULD be fighting on one side are slowly pulled towards another <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
