&lt;chuckle&gt; A question I am commonly asked as well, and the same answer -- it is up to the individual <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Unless you are in a Good[evil][neutral] only guild, then grouping with (at least) a Neutral should not be a problem.  In fact, there are times in much fantasy literature where Good/Evil grouped together, to achieve a common short-term objective.  Mind you, the personal goals of both sides are different, but the short-term goal must be accomplished.  With that being the case, I can even see it happening in Norrath (again, for specific cases).  Such a grouping could provide much good RP oppurtunities, in the short term (specific mission) and the long, as the Good and Evil meet again and again, trying to exploit/convert the other, kill the other, etc. <br>
<br>
My guild is based on the foundations of Tunare AND Justice --- and as such accepts any non-evil alignment, so long as they follow the tenets of one or the other (preferrably both <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
&lt;shrug&gt; I know different people have different ideas on what is good/bad RP, but I would be interested in hearing your opinions (flames, whatever &lt;wink&gt;)<br>
